284
00:10:35,144 --> 00:10:36,837
-Ah!

285
00:10:36,837 --> 00:10:38,172
-J.P.!

286
00:10:48,415 --> 00:10:50,384
Execute!

287
00:10:50,417 --> 00:10:51,518
Spirit Evolution!

288
00:11:10,437 --> 00:11:11,772
Lobomon!

289
00:11:11,805 --> 00:11:13,073
-Wha?

290
00:11:15,442 --> 00:11:18,078
-It's Lobomon.

291
00:11:18,078 --> 00:11:20,447
-That is no way to
treat a lady.

292
00:11:20,481 --> 00:11:23,050
Didn't your parents teach
you any manners?

293
00:11:23,083 --> 00:11:25,753
-And so, the fourth
hath joined us.

294
00:11:29,757 --> 00:11:31,725
-Hang on, you guys.

295
00:11:31,759 --> 00:11:32,760
We're coming!

296
00:11:40,660 --> 00:11:41,962
-Hehe heheheh.

297
00:11:46,166 --> 00:11:47,167
-Enough.

298
00:11:51,037 --> 00:11:53,640
-They can't be much further.
(THINKING) Please

299
00:11:53,640 --> 00:11:55,308
let them be all right.

300
00:11:55,342 --> 00:11:56,977
Lobo Kendo!

301
00:11:56,977 --> 00:11:58,945
NEEMON (OFFSCREEN): I'm
getting shoulder sick.

302
00:11:58,979 --> 00:11:59,846
BOKOMON (OFFSCREEN):
Who cares?

303
00:11:59,913 --> 00:12:01,348
My baby's half scrambled.

304
00:12:01,414 --> 00:12:03,650
-I think not.

305
00:12:03,683 --> 00:12:06,620
Dark Reflection!

306
00:12:06,653 --> 00:12:07,821
-Ah!

307
00:12:07,821 --> 00:12:10,123
NEEMON (OFFSCREEN): Wee,
I'm all dizzy.

308
00:12:10,156 --> 00:12:12,058
-Heh heh.

309
00:12:12,092 --> 00:12:13,126
-Hi honey!

310
00:12:15,762 --> 00:12:17,030
Acid Ink!

311
00:12:22,235 --> 00:12:24,337
-Yeah, you're quite a lady.

312
00:12:32,579 --> 00:12:34,381
-So, where are they?

313
00:12:34,381 --> 00:12:36,049
Lobomon!

314
00:12:36,082 --> 00:12:37,517
-Oh my.

315
00:12:37,550 --> 00:12:40,787
He's taking on Mercurymon and
Calmaramon all by himself.

316
00:12:40,820 --> 00:12:43,890
-Bokomon, why are the others
stuck to that wall?

317
00:12:43,957 --> 00:12:46,359
-They've been captured,
you witless nit.

318
00:12:46,393 --> 00:12:47,694
-Guys!

319
00:12:47,761 --> 00:12:49,262
-Wait!

320
00:12:49,262 --> 00:12:50,296
-Howling Laser!

321
00:12:55,301 --> 00:12:57,137
-Lobomon needs our help!

322
00:12:57,170 --> 00:12:58,605
-But what can we do?

323
00:12:58,605 --> 00:12:59,806
-Man, if only we could
Spirit Evolve.

324
00:13:03,343 --> 00:13:06,112
Hey, you better not throw
our D-Tectors in there.

325
00:13:08,948 --> 00:13:10,650
-Now what?

326
00:13:10,717 --> 00:13:11,951
-I'm gonna need a plan.

327
00:13:14,854 --> 00:13:16,456
-Tell me something.

328
00:13:16,523 --> 00:13:19,025
It's obvious you don't care
about yourself, but can you

329
00:13:19,059 --> 00:13:20,627
promise me the others
won't get hurt?

330
00:13:20,627 --> 00:13:23,029
If you can't, then we'd better
just go home now, because I

331
00:13:23,063 --> 00:13:24,998
won't let you risk
their lives.

332
00:13:24,998 --> 00:13:28,034
-I'm gonna need to do
this carefully.

333
00:13:28,068 --> 00:13:29,536
-That would be nice.

334
00:13:29,569 --> 00:13:32,138
-I can't just jump in without
thinking first.

335
00:13:32,172 --> 00:13:35,141
Tommy and the others can't
Spirit Evolve, and if those

336
00:13:35,175 --> 00:13:37,811
two goons get their hands
on them, they

337
00:13:37,844 --> 00:13:38,845
won't stand a chance.

338
00:13:38,878 --> 00:13:40,814
I'll need Lobomon's help.

339
00:13:40,847 --> 00:13:42,348
-I think he might need yours.

340
00:13:42,382 --> 00:13:43,683
Look!

341
00:13:48,121 --> 00:13:49,089
-Hurry, Takuya.

342
00:13:49,122 --> 00:13:49,656
Hurry.

343
00:13:49,689 --> 00:13:50,924
Run like the wind.

344
00:13:57,464 --> 00:14:00,567
-Oh sweetie, don't tell me your
done playing with me.

345
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:03,103
-Maybe the poor lad just needs
a bit of refreshment.

346
00:14:03,136 --> 00:14:05,705
-You are so thoughtful.

347
00:14:05,738 --> 00:14:08,041
One drink of water
coming right up.

348
00:14:08,074 --> 00:14:09,075
Draining Rain!

349
00:14:12,912 --> 00:14:13,913
-All right.

350
00:14:13,913 --> 00:14:15,615
I want you two to stay here.

351
00:14:15,682 --> 00:14:17,717
-But what are you gonna do?

352
00:14:17,751 --> 00:14:19,085
-Wait until the time is right.

353
00:14:19,085 --> 00:14:20,754
-Well, when is that?

354
00:14:20,820 --> 00:14:23,723
So, we ran all this way and my
tummy got upset for nothing?

355
00:14:23,756 --> 00:14:24,924
-All right, quiet please.

356
00:14:24,991 --> 00:14:27,427
I have a feeling Takuya
is right.

357
00:14:27,494 --> 00:14:28,461
-Really?

358
00:14:28,495 --> 00:14:29,796
OK.

359
00:14:29,796 --> 00:14:30,296
-(THINKING) That smell.

360
00:14:30,296 --> 00:14:31,798
The sound.

361
00:14:31,831 --> 00:14:35,401
The atmosphere is changing.

362
00:14:35,468 --> 00:14:38,138
-This doesn't seem like
Takuya at all.

363
00:14:38,138 --> 00:14:40,140
It's as if he's become
different somehow.

364
00:14:45,745 --> 00:14:48,615
-A storm is coming.

365
00:14:48,648 --> 00:14:49,816
-What kind of storm?

366
00:14:49,816 --> 00:14:52,118
-I don't know.

367
00:14:52,152 --> 00:14:53,953
(THINKING) I thought Takuya
had some sort of plan.

368
00:14:53,987 --> 00:14:55,822
He certainly thought about
it long enough.

369
00:14:55,889 --> 00:14:57,290
But now I'm not so sure.

370
00:14:57,323 --> 00:14:59,659
All this waiting and wondering
about the weather.

371
00:14:59,659 --> 00:15:00,627
Who cares about the weather?

372
00:15:00,660 --> 00:15:02,028
The others are in danger.

373
00:15:09,435 --> 00:15:10,870
-Have you no control?

374
00:15:10,870 --> 00:15:12,405
-Why are you mad at me?

375
00:15:12,438 --> 00:15:13,406
It was your idea.

376
00:15:13,439 --> 00:15:15,742
-Ugh, I'm surrounded
by buffoons.

377
00:15:20,380 --> 00:15:21,381
-Lobomon!

378
00:15:21,381 --> 00:15:24,584
-Give me your best shot.

379
00:15:24,651 --> 00:15:27,453
-As you wish.

380
00:15:27,487 --> 00:15:31,291
Ha ha ha.

381
00:15:31,324 --> 00:15:33,393
-Look there is a storm.

382
00:15:33,459 --> 00:15:35,762
-(THINKING) Wind.

383
00:15:35,795 --> 00:15:37,363
I'm getting stronger.

384
00:15:41,968 --> 00:15:43,736
-Well, what do you know?

385
00:15:43,770 --> 00:15:44,938
Takuya was right.

386
00:15:44,971 --> 00:15:46,606
-Yes, but how could
he have known?

387
00:15:46,639 --> 00:15:50,610
-(THINKING) And a little snow.

388
00:15:50,643 --> 00:15:52,612
Right now!

389
00:15:52,612 --> 00:15:55,949
-You're freaking me out.

390
00:15:55,982 --> 00:15:57,617
-Oh, that's cold.

391
00:15:57,617 --> 00:15:58,952
-Wind and snow.

392
00:15:58,985 --> 00:16:01,588
Thunder and lightning.

393
00:16:01,621 --> 00:16:04,591
Forces of nature lend
us your strength!

394
00:16:04,624 --> 00:16:07,627
-He's talking to the weather
and it's listening.

395
00:16:07,627 --> 00:16:11,097
-Now I understand what it
means to be a Digimon!

396
00:16:11,164 --> 00:16:14,334
I'm ready to accept the
responsibility that comes with

397
00:16:14,334 --> 00:16:15,702
great power.

398
00:16:15,735 --> 00:16:19,872
To truly become Agunimon,
Warrior of Flame!

399
00:16:23,843 --> 00:16:25,845
-Had enough?

400
00:16:25,845 --> 00:16:27,180
-Leave him alone!

401
00:16:27,180 --> 00:16:29,682
-Oh, can it.

402
00:16:29,716 --> 00:16:33,253
At least, the final player
hath arrived.

403
00:16:33,286 --> 00:16:36,489
-Then let's get this
show on the road.

404
00:16:36,522 --> 00:16:38,024
-Pyro Dirt.

405
00:16:38,091 --> 00:16:41,995
-Missed me, missed me,
now you gotta k--

406
00:16:42,061 --> 00:16:43,730
-Thanks, but no thanks.

407
00:16:43,730 --> 00:16:48,735
-That little whelp is much
stronger than I remember.

408
00:16:48,735 --> 00:16:50,069
-Pyro Tornado!

409
00:17:01,077 --> 00:17:03,780
Now Lobomon, free the others!

410
00:17:03,846 --> 00:17:04,914
-Lobo Kendo!

411
00:17:08,584 --> 00:17:09,318
-All right, guys.

412
00:17:09,352 --> 00:17:10,419
It's your turn.

413
00:17:20,696 --> 00:17:22,665
-Execute!

414
00:17:22,698 --> 00:17:24,100
Spirit Evolution!

415
00:17:42,318 --> 00:17:43,319
-Beetlemon!

416
00:17:58,601 --> 00:17:59,869
-Kozemon!

417
00:18:16,552 --> 00:18:19,121
-Kumamon.

418
00:18:19,155 --> 00:18:21,958
-Ah, isn't this sweet?

419
00:18:21,991 --> 00:18:23,759
Together at last.

420
00:18:23,759 --> 00:18:25,261
I love reunions.

421
00:18:25,294 --> 00:18:26,963
Ha ha.

422
00:18:26,996 --> 00:18:30,132
It appears it's time for the
final act of our little play.

423
00:18:30,166 --> 00:18:33,269
-I should put on something
more appropriate.

424
00:18:33,302 --> 00:18:36,239
Ranamon Slide Evolution!

425
00:18:36,272 --> 00:18:38,774
Calmaramon!

426
00:18:38,774 --> 00:18:40,610
-You don't really think
you can win?

427
00:18:40,610 --> 00:18:41,944
Haven't you heard?

428
00:18:41,978 --> 00:18:44,480
It's not nice to mess
with Mother Nature!

429
00:18:44,547 --> 00:18:45,448
-Let's finish this.

430
00:18:45,448 --> 00:18:46,749
Thunder Fist!

431
00:18:50,887 --> 00:18:52,188
-Tempest Twist!

432
00:18:55,391 --> 00:18:57,660
-Argh, what is going on?

433
00:18:57,693 --> 00:19:00,496
-Blizzard Blaster!

434
00:19:00,530 --> 00:19:01,497
-Ah!

435
00:19:01,497 --> 00:19:02,832
-Lobo Kendo!

436
00:19:05,902 --> 00:19:08,037
-How did y'all get so strong?

437
00:19:08,070 --> 00:19:12,041
-We have a stronger ally than
you could ever imagine.

438
00:19:12,108 --> 00:19:14,043
-Odds bodkins!

439
00:19:14,110 --> 00:19:15,544
They're using the forces
of nature to

440
00:19:15,611 --> 00:19:17,013
amplify their attacks.

441
00:19:17,013 --> 00:19:18,548
The master will be displeased.

442
00:19:18,614 --> 00:19:19,749
RANAMON (OFFSCREEN):
Forget the master!

443
00:19:19,782 --> 00:19:21,684
What about us?

444
00:19:21,684 --> 00:19:23,653
-Will you stop sniveling,
woman?

445
00:19:23,686 --> 00:19:24,987
-Argh!

446
00:19:27,924 --> 00:19:31,561
You won't defeat
us ever again!

447
00:19:31,561 --> 00:19:37,567
[screaming]

448
00:19:37,600 --> 00:19:40,369
-Ah, I just love the theater.

449
00:19:40,403 --> 00:19:41,070
Takuya

450
00:19:41,070 --> 00:19:42,071
-Takuya, my boy.

451
00:19:42,071 --> 00:19:43,105
You've matured.

452
00:19:46,943 --> 00:19:49,545
-Well, now what do we do?

453
00:19:49,579 --> 00:19:50,580
-Retreat and regroup.

454
00:19:54,083 --> 00:19:55,651
-You little brats.

455
00:19:55,685 --> 00:19:58,988
This isn't over!

456
00:19:59,021 --> 00:20:00,256
-Yeah!

457
00:20:03,626 --> 00:20:06,062
-That is the last time that I
listen to you, Mercurymon.

458
00:20:06,128 --> 00:20:08,965
You should've let
me squash them.

459
00:20:08,965 --> 00:20:12,001
-The little humans are smarter
than I thought, but fret not,

460
00:20:12,034 --> 00:20:15,604
m'lady, for within me,
a plan is hatching.

461
00:20:15,638 --> 00:20:18,808
All we need is a more
advantageous location to spin

462
00:20:18,808 --> 00:20:20,509
our web of woe.

463
00:20:20,576 --> 00:20:22,144
-I'm so sorry, you guys.

464
00:20:22,178 --> 00:20:23,612
This was all my fault.

465
00:20:23,646 --> 00:20:25,314
-What are you talking about?

466
00:20:25,348 --> 00:20:27,316
You're the one who rescued us.

467
00:20:27,316 --> 00:20:27,817
-But--

468
00:20:27,883 --> 00:20:29,485
-It's OK, Takuya.

469
00:20:29,552 --> 00:20:32,955
We were worried about you, but
I knew you'd come through.

470
00:20:32,989 --> 00:20:35,057
-I guess I really owe
you one, Koji.

471
00:20:35,091 --> 00:20:37,193
